CONTRIBUTING.rst.message:
Few days ago I already proposed to merge these changes and those of the oslo policy (c.f my comment in [1]), but I agree with Ben's comment in [1] it could be more appropriate to update the standard contribution guide to highlight some specific parts like the git/gerrit part.

I propose to you the following road map:
1. we keep only the pre-commit part here (mechanismes + contribution guide related parts);
2. we merge these changes;
3. we spread the pre-commit features on oslo.*;
4. we update the oslo contribution guide [1] with a follow up patch to speak about pre-commit;
5. we drop the pre-commit doc part here.

Thoughts?

[1] https://review.opendev.org/#/c/723044/

